{"word":"δημαγωγέω","slug":"δημαγωγέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δημαγωγέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:δημαγωγός'><el>δημαγωγός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to lead the people</i>, in bad sense, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to win by popular arts</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}